{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"83dc7d64-6d7e-457d-a202-ecd42ce0f5ef","content":"For a .NET Web API with authentication, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth <option>\n```\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Azure AD for a single tenant |\n| `MultiOrg` | Azure AD for multiple tenants |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate authentication |\n\n**Common examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Basic API, no auth\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n\n# Azure AD single-tenant auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com -n MyApi\n\n# Azure AD B2C\ndotnet new webapi --auth IndividualB2C -n MyApi\n```\n\nFor **JWT bearer** or **API key** auth not tied to Azure AD, start with `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWant me to scaffold a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a2574a7e-a5c1-400e-9b36-a973b1fc5cdb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This seems like a general .NET question. Let me check if there's relevant content in the repository that might help, but this also seems like a general knowledge question I can answer directly.\n\nLet me check the repository for any relevant dotnet templates or skills.","outputTokens":346,"requestId":"33C8:13D2B1:1E084C8:21D40BA:69E8195C"},"id":"349b72b8-8a07-441b-983a-0459009909cc","timestamp":"2026-04-22T00:42:13.037Z","parentId":"eaeb40e1-e635-441d-9664-e531705034da"}
